<main>
  <!-- Overview -->
  <section class="pt-120 pb-4" style="background: url('/images/hero-1-bg.jpg') no-repeat fixed center center/cover;">
    <div class="mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:max-w-7xl lg:px-8 my-16">
      <h1 class="text-interface-500 text-center font-bold text-4xl leading-normal lg:text-5xl capitalize lg:leading-snug">
        The Power of Augmented Staffing in Tech: A CTO's Perspective
      </h1>
    </div>
  </section>
  <!--/ Overview -->
  <!-- Entry -->
  <section class="py-20 lg:py-12">
    <div class="mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:max-w-3xl lg:px-8">
      <p class="text-interface-500 my-6">
        When I step into a company at its early stages, one of the primary strategies I advocate for is augmented staffing. For those unfamiliar with the term, augmented staffing revolves around a simple yet powerful idea: directly interviewing, hiring, and managing contractors as though they are full-time employees. If these contractors come through a vendor, then consider the vendor as their HR representative. This approach offers a myriad of benefits that can significantly impact the trajectory of your project. Here's a closer look:
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-interface-500 my-6 text-2xl font-bold">
        Augmented Staffing Provides Complete Ownership
      </h2>

      <p class="text-interface-500 my-6">
        Augmented staffing empowers you with unparalleled control over your project. This methodology allows you to assemble a team that wholly resonates with your vision, ensuring every facet of the endeavor mirrors your brand's identity and goals.
      </p>

      <p class="text-interface-500 my-6">
        In contrast, working with agencies can be more restrictive. Pivots become cumbersome, and your interactions are typically funneled through a Project Manager rather than the actual talent executing the work. Moreover, with agencies, your ownership of the product might be delayed until the final payment is processed. Curious about reviewing the code to validate its quality? With agencies, such transparency might be elusive.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-interface-500 my-6 text-2xl font-bold">
        Seamless Collaboration
      </h2>

      <p class="text-interface-500 my-6">
        One of the standout features of augmented staffing is the intimacy of collaboration it fosters. This direct relationship with your extended team facilitates streamlined communication, efficient workflows, and expedited development cycles. When liaising with agencies, additional layers of communication might introduce delays or misinterpretations.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-interface-500 my-6 text-2xl font-bold">
        Cost Efficiency
      </h2>

      <p class="text-interface-500 my-6">
        For budding businesses, every dollar counts. Augmented staffing stands out as a cost-conscious choice. By directly governing your team, you not only retain control over the project's financials but also sidestep the added fees typically associated with agencies. These entities often factor in overheads and profit margins that can inflate costs.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-interface-500 my-6 text-2xl font-bold">
        Consistent Staffing
      </h2>

      <p class="text-interface-500 my-6">
        Consistency is key in tech projects. With agencies, the team you initially onboard may not be around for subsequent phases or maintenance. This inconsistency can birth communication challenges and a loss of valuable knowledge. Augmented staffing, on the other hand, promotes stability. It allows the core team that initiated the project to persistently support, understand, and nurture it, guaranteeing sustained success.
      </p>

      <p class="text-interface-500 my-6">
        While these insights are shaped by my personal experiences, it's essential to note that outcomes might vary based on specific circumstances. It's also worth mentioning that if you're unfamiliar with the nuances of hiring and vetting tech professionals, having someone with expertise on board—even if just for a few hours a week—can be invaluable. After all, the right guidance can transform good projects into great successes.
      </p>

      <h2>Attention: Drawbacks!</h2>

      <p class="text-interface-500 my-6">
        Here's the thing. Without a seasoned technical leader at the helm, companies may face misaligned goals, inefficient workflows, and potential pitfalls in talent vetting.
      </p>

      <p class="text-interface-500 my-6">
        Quality agencies (which can be hard to find and vet) offer partners to bridge that gap, and if you don't have a Technical Partner, this can be appealing.
      </p>

      <p class="text-interface-500 my-6">
        So the question becomes, do you want hire an agency for a one-and-done project? Or do you want to bring on staff and build your business and fully own the process?
      </p>

    </div>
  </section>
